<L>__{exterior dry creek lodge late in the day}
<A>__{a beautiful old colonial mansion, nestled in the mountains and forests of the north west. romantic and from another day. charlie and harriet pull up in front of it. the valets open the door for them.}
<C>__{harriet}
<D>__{it's like a castle, charlie. it's so beautiful.}
<C>__{valet}
<D>__{welcome to the dry creek. you just beat the rainstorm. two hours later and the roads'd probably be closed.}
<C>__{charlie}
<D>__{great. if you could help us with the luggage, we have these two in the back seat and...}
<A>__{as they deal with the luggage, harriet starts to walk away from the hotel, away from the car, rain falling on her head. she walks straight at the camera, so only we can see her expression. her expression is one of simply "losing it".}
<C>__{charlie}
<D>__{harriet? what are you doing honey?}
<A>__{harriet turns around and smiles at charlie. he smiles back.}
